{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EBSoTZ8mAiqNji8SbZX1tY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the current setup:\n- 3 existing Elasticsearch nodes (es-0, es-1, es-2) running as a StatefulSet named \"es\"\n- They use a shared ConfigMap \"es-config\" with elasticsearch.yml\n- The cluster has xpack security enabled with SSL/TLS\n\nI need to:\n1. Add 2 new data nodes with different allocation attributes than the existing nodes\n2. Ensure shards for \"app-data\" index relocate to new nodes\n3. Keep cluster healthy (yellow/green with 5 nodes)\n4. Keep the es-cluster StatefulSet at 3 replicas\n\nMy approach is to create a separate StatefulSet for the new data nodes with distinct allocation attributes, then configure index routing to move the \"app-data\" shards to them. But I need to be careful about modifying the existing nodes—that would require a rolling restart of the current StatefulSet, which could disrupt the cluster.\n\nInstead, I'll update the ConfigMap for the existing nodes to add an allocation attribute, create a new ConfigMap and StatefulSet for the 2 new data nodes with a different attribute, and once they're healthy, configure the index to route to the new nodes. Let me check the current cluster state and index configuration first.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3657,"cache_read_input_tokens":29235,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3657},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c07c6bf5-d4c0-4186-9a9c-82051ee79943","uuid":"ea59d947-c118-4e3c-a97d-7a0aaeed0f64","request_id":"req_011CcLdYBKwkpkkYZMbtmdJp"}
